
= Software.coop has members in London, Norfolk, Somerset, Berkshire, Cumbria and Edinburgh; formed 2002, the co-op hosts sites, develops web apps and managers servers for most sectors (including commercial); committed to Free and Open Source Software, the co-op includes a debian developer and a former Koha release manager; 


URL = http://www.software.coop/


=Description=

CyberUnion Podcast, interview with MJ Ray of Software Coop:


"How does it work?

    
Production  but consensus decision-making as far as possible   – we are a collective (we fired the boss)  but other co-ops like The Co-operative Group  and JohnLewis Partnership look more like other hierarchical businesses.


What industry is your coop a part of?

    
We’re a Tech Worker Co-op… that is, we do tech and the workers are the members who run the co-op


What service or business does your coop take part in?

http://koha-community.org/
http://www.wordpress.org/
http://www.djangoproject.com/
http://www.debian.org/


How do we relate to other co-ops?

    
Our co-ops is a member of other co-ordinating co-ops like http://www.scotland.coop/ and http://www.uk.coop/
        
We prefer to trade with other co-ops, but most of our business is still with private businesses.
    

What is a coop?
    
Formal internationally-agreed definition: http://www.ica.coop/coop/principles.html "

(http://cyberunions.org/cyberunions-podcast-episode-54-this-is-what-democracy-looks-like-in-a-workplace)


